All results from tick-by-tick JavaScript simulation matching exact C code logic.

### play_block at initial playback start:
| Scenario | BPM | recTicks | M | nb | play_block | Status |
|----------|-----|----------|---|----|------------|--------|
| short rec | 120 | 50 | 690 | 690 | 4 | OK (within crossfade) |
| 1phrase overshoot | 120 | 700 | 690 | 690 | 11 | OK (snaps at boundary) |
| exact boundary | 120 | 690 | 690 | 690 | 4 | OK |
| 2phrase overshoot | 120 | 1500 | 690 | 1380 | 121 | OK (snaps at boundary) |
| short rec | 105 | 50 | 789 | 789 | 4 | OK |
| 3phrase | 140 | 2200 | 591 | 2364 | 4 | OK |

### play_block at phrase boundary (all clips):
All BPMs tested: play_block = 0 at clip boundary = phrase boundary. PASS.

### Drift after 1000 loops:
120/105/90/140/180/60 BPM: all PASS (play_block matches formula exactly).
